Description: Fragment ofoval handle to sharpish turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay near fine pink-brown; dull yellow slip.
Curator's comments: Name Pasion. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.122, 4. From the same die as Athens, Agora SS12327.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0601)
